---
import DocuLayout from "../layouts/DocuLayout.astro";
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<DocuLayout>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Introduction to MonkeyJs</h1>
  <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-700">
    Welcome to the official documentation for MonkeyJs, a lightweight, customizable product tour library 
    that helps you create interactive guided tours for your web applications.
  </p>
  
  <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">What is MonkeyJs?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">
        MonkeyJs is a framework-agnostic touring library designed to help developers 
        create intuitive, step-by-step guides for their applications. Whether you're 
        onboarding new users, highlighting new features, or providing contextual help,
        MonkeyJs makes it easy to create engaging tours with minimal effort.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">Key Features</h2>
      <ul class="mt-2 ml-6 list-disc text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Framework agnostic with dedicated implementations for TypeScript and React</li>
        <li>Customizable UI with flexible theming options</li>
        <li>Simple API for defining tour steps and behaviors</li>
        <li>Lightweight and performant</li>
        <li>Developer-friendly with strong TypeScript support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">Getting Started</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">
        Check out our <a href="/docs/setup" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Setup Guide</a> to 
        start creating your first tour, or explore the documentation to learn more about the library's capabilities.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocuLayout>
